headlines.description: — Ziaire Williams and GG Jackson scored 27 points apiece, and the Memphis Grizzlies held on for a 113-110 victory over the Milwaukee Bucks on Thursday night in the last game for both teams before the All-Star break.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ziaire Williams, GG Jackson score 27 points apiece as Grizzlies hang on for 113-110 win over Bucks

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson came off the bench for the first time since his rookie season to knock down seven 3-pointers and score a season-high 35 points, leading the Golden State Warriors to a 140-137 victory over the Utah Jazz on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Warriors ride Thompson's big game off the bench to 140-137 victory over Jazz

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 34 points and the Minnesota Timberwolves built a 30-point lead after the most lopsided first quarter in the NBA this season, handing the Portland Trail Blazers a sixth straight loss with a 128-91 rout on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Timberwolves jump out to a 30-point lead over Blazers and finish with a 128-91 victory
